SALESFORCE RELEASE NOTES
Establish Contract Terms for Supplier Cost Recovery

Use contracts to drive collaboration with your suppliers and mutually agree on supplier recovery terms. Specify the price that a supplier pays for a causal part, whether a part must be returned to a supplier, and the recovery terms for repairs and replacements. The claimed amount for supplier recovery claims is automatically derived from the contract.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions with Manufacturing Cloud. The user interface of this product is available in English only and may not be fully supported in other languages.

Who: This feature is available to users with the Warranty Lifecycle Management and Claims Foundation permission sets.

How: Enter into a contract with a supplier to define the supplier recovery terms. Stipulate the recovery terms in the supplier contract to determine the payout.
